          "datePublished": "2023-10-21",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "\"Based on reviews and feedback from current parents and students, our decision to enroll our children in this school has been disappointing & education level is dropped. The quality of education and student behavior has not met our expectations. There have been instances of children using inappropriate language (bad words), frequent complaints about bullying, and a lack of sports activities & there are chargeable activities we have to pay else the PT period is name sake. No the school appears more business-oriented. It seems that the teachers may struggle to manage the children effectively, and there is a gap in providing contemporary education and fostering self-awareness to students. Hope they may look to improvements in all the area. and on admission, we encourage anyone considering this school to visit in person and assess the situation before entrusting their children's future to it. Jai Hind Jai Bharath.\"",
